      "title": "Thunderstorms and heavy rain expected in Mississauga today",
      "summary": "Storm activity may develop through the morning and continue into the afternoon, with the greatest risk for impacts expected later in the day. The Toronto and Region Conservation Authority (TRCA) has issued a Flood Outlook Statement , and Environment and Climate Change Canada (ECCC) has issued a Yellow Level Severe Thunderstorm Watch for the area. Residents should be prepared for rapidly changing weather conditions, including heavy rain, strong winds and localized flooding.",
